          "text": "of this section. If a county does not notify the director, or notifies the director that the county will not administer and enforce all or parts of certain specialty codes under the building inspection program, the director shall contract with a municipality or other person or use such state employees or state agencies as are necessary to administer and enforce those codes or parts of the codes, and permit or other fees arising from the administration and enforcement must be paid into the Consumer and Business Services Fund created by ORS 705.145 and credited to the account responsible for paying such expenses. A state employee may not be displaced as a result of using contract personnel.",
          "subsections": []
        },
        {
          "label": "(7)",
          "token": "7",
          "kind": "numeric",
          "text": "If a municipality administering a building inspection program under this section seeks to administer additional parts of a program, the municipality must comply with ORS 455.148, including the requirement that the municipality administer and enforce all aspects of the building inspection program. Thereafter, the municipality is subject to ORS 455.148 and ceases to be subject to this section.",
          "subsections": []
        },
        {
          "label": "(8)",
          "token": "8",
          "kind": "numeric",
          "text": "The department shall adopt rules to require the governing body of each municipality to submit a written plan with the notice required under subsection",
          "subsections": []
        },
        {
          "label": "(9)",
          "token": "9",
          "kind": "numeric",
          "text": "A municipality that administers a code for which persons or businesses are authorized under ORS 455.457 to perform activities shall recognize and accept those activities as if performed by the municipality. A municipality is not required to accept an inspection, a plan or a plan review that does not meet the requirements of the state building code.",
          "subsections": []
        },
        {
          "label": "(10)",
          "token": "10",
          "kind": "numeric",
          "text": "The department or a municipality that accepts an inspection or plan review as required by this section by a person licensed under ORS 455.457 has no responsibility or liability for the activities of the licensee.",
          "subsections": []
        },
        {
          "label": "(11)",
          "token": "11",
          "kind": "numeric",
          "text": "In addition to the requirements of ORS 455.100 and 455.110, the director shall regulate building inspection programs of municipalities assumed prior to January 1, 2002. Regulation under this subsection must include but not be limited to:",
          "subsections": [
            {
              "label": "(a)",
              "token": "a",
              "kind": "alpha_lower",
              "text": "Creating building inspection program application and amendment requirements and procedures;",
              "subsections": []
            },
            {
              "label": "(b)",
              "token": "b",
              "kind": "alpha_lower",
              "text": "Granting or denying applications for building inspection program authority and amendments;",
              "subsections": []
            },
            {
              "label": "(c)",
              "token": "c",
              "kind": "alpha_lower",
              "text": "Reviewing procedures and program operations of municipalities;",
              "subsections": []
            },
            {
              "label": "(d)",
              "token": "d",
              "kind": "alpha_lower",
              "text": "Creating standards for efficient, effective, timely and acceptable building inspection programs;",
              "subsections": []
            },
            {
              "label": "(e)",
              "token": "e",
              "kind": "alpha_lower",
              "text": "Creating standards for justifying increases in building inspection program fees adopted by a municipality;",
              "subsections": []
            },
            {
              "label": "(f)",
              "token": "f",
              "kind": "alpha_lower",
              "text": "Creating standards for determining whether a county or department building inspection program is economically impaired because of the countys or the departments inability to reasonably continue providing the program or part of the program throughout a county, if another municipality is allowed to provide a building inspection program or part of a program within the same county; and",
              "subsections": []
            },
            {
              "label": "(g)",
              "token": "g",
              "kind": "alpha_lower",
              "text": "Enforcing the requirements of this section.",
              "subsections": []
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "label": "(12)",
          "token": "12",
          "kind": "numeric",
          "text": "The department may assume administration and enforcement of a building inspection program:",
          "subsections": [
            {
              "label": "(a)",
              "token": "a",
              "kind": "alpha_lower",
              "text": "During the pendency of activities under ORS 455.770;",
              "subsections": []
            },
            {
              "label": "(b)",
              "token": "b",
              "kind": "alpha_lower",
              "text": "If a municipality abandons any part of the building inspection program or is no longer able to administer the building inspection program; or",
              "subsections": []
            },
            {
              "label": "(c)",
              "token": "c",
              "kind": "alpha_lower",
              "text": "If a municipality fails to substantially comply with any provision of this section or of ORS 455.465, 455.467 and 455.469.",
              "subsections": []
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "label": "(13)",
          "token": "13",
          "kind": "numeric",
          "text": "If the department assumes the administration and enforcement of a building inspection program under this section, in addition to any other power granted to the director, the director may:",
          "subsections": [
            {
              "label": "(a)",
              "token": "a",
              "kind": "alpha_lower",
              "text": "Enter into agreements with local governments under ORS 455.185 regarding the administration and enforcement of the assumed building inspection program;",
              "subsections": []
            },
            {
              "label": "(b)",
              "token": "b",
              "kind": "alpha_lower",
              "text": "Take action as described in ORS 455.192 to ensure that sufficient staff and other resources are available for the administration and enforcement of the assumed building inspection program;",
              "subsections": []
            },
            {
              "label": "(c)",
              "token": "c",
              "kind": "alpha_lower",
              "text": "Charge fees described in ORS 455.195 for department services provided in administering and enforcing the assumed building inspection program; and",
              "subsections": []
            },
            {
              "label": "(d)",
              "token": "d",
              "kind": "alpha_lower",
              "text": "Ratify or disapprove the discretionary decisions of a contract building official, as both terms are defined in ORS 455.202, to the extent that a municipality could ratify or disapprove the discretionary decisions of the municipalitys contract building official.",
              "subsections": []
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "label": "(14)",
          "token": "14",
          "kind": "numeric",
          "text": "If a municipality abandons or otherwise ceases to administer all or part of a building inspection program described in this section, the municipality may not resume the administration and enforcement of the abandoned program or part of a program for at least two years. The municipality may resume the administration and enforcement of the abandoned program or part of a program only on July 1 of an odd-numbered year. To resume the administration and enforcement of the abandoned program or part of a program, the municipality must comply with ORS 455.148, including the requirement that the municipality administer and enforce all aspects of the building inspection program. Thereafter, the municipality is subject to ORS 455.148 and ceases to be subject to this section.",
